headline: Electronic Arts (EA): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: Over the past six months, Electronic Arts has been a great trade, beating the S&P 500 by 12%. Its stock price has climbed to $200.22, representing a healthy 37.5% increase. This run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
